New Records: Travis Head scored the highest score by an Australian in a one-day match played in England (154 not out)
Key Match Events: Travis Head scored an unbeaten 154 off 129 balls
Marnus Labuschagne took 3 wickets for 39 and also took 4 catches
Adam Zampa took 3 wickets to halt England's progress
Post-Match Reflections: Mitch Marsh said he was very happy with the win
Travis Head expressed satisfaction with his performance and credited his relaxed approach to the game
Miscellaneous Highlights: England's top order went after Adam Zampa initially but he later found his innings-wrecking form
Jamie Smith was caught at cover by Steve Smith for 23
